%matplotlib inline

Helper for color labels

str2labels[source]

str2labels(s)

Label image from a multiline string.

Converts a multiline string to a height x width x 3 label image. The string may consists of digits 0-9 and one of: . k r g b c m y o w See below for examples. Args: s: a multiline string to be converted to labels.

Returns: numpy array of shape height x width x 3

Some simple label examples

Pyramid Benchmark Pictures 

import combinatorial.label_zoo
all_label_strings = [l for l in combinatorial.label_zoo.__all__ if l[:3] == 'L2_']
all_label_strings;

for label_id in all_label_strings:
    label_string = eval (label_id)
    img = str2labels (label_string)
    plt.figure()
    plt.imshow (img)
    plt.title (label_id)
    plt.xticks([])
    plt.yticks([])
    plt.show()
    plt.close()

for label_id in all_label_strings [:]:
    label_string = eval (label_id)
    labels = str2labels (label_string)
    
    lm = LabelMap.from_labels (labels)

    print (f'{label_id:30}: {lm.n_darts:4} d / {lm.no_0_cells:3} p / {lm.no_1_cells:3} e / {lm.no_2_cells:3} f', end=' ')

    lm.remove_edges()
    lm.remove_vertices()

    print (f'-> {lm.n_darts:3} d / {lm.no_0_cells:2} p / {lm.no_1_cells:2} e / {lm.no_2_cells:2} f')

for label_id in all_label_strings [:]:
    label_string = eval (label_id)
    labels = str2labels (label_string)
    
    lm = LabelMap.from_labels (labels)

    plt.figure (figsize=(3*lm.n_cols, 3*lm.n_rows))
    
    plt.subplot (121)
    lm.plot()
    plt.title (f'{label_id}\n{lm.n_darts} d / {lm.no_0_cells} p / {lm.no_1_cells} e / {lm.no_2_cells} f')

    plt.subplot (122)

    
    lm.remove_edges()
#     logging.getLogger().setLevel("DEBUG")
    lm.remove_vertices()
    lm.plot(number_darts=True)
    
    plt.title (f'{label_id}\n{lm.n_darts} d / {lm.no_0_cells} p / {lm.no_1_cells} e / {lm.no_2_cells} f')
    
    plt.show()
    plt.close()
